      Subinterfaces of Environmental in com.planet_ink.coffee_mud.Abilities.interfaces 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  Ability
      The basic interface for all skills, spells, chants, prayers, and properties.
      interface  CraftorAbility
      This interface denotes an ability that also incidentally is capable of generating objects, usually items.
      interface  DiseaseAffect
      DiseaseAffect is an ability interface to denote those properties, affects, or Disease objects that act as curable physical diseases.
      interface  ExtendableAbility
      An ExtendableAbility is an ability/effect object that can be more easily extended in code at runtime using various methods that add internal pointers to coded solutions to it's external api.
      interface  HealthCondition
      HealthCondition is an ability interface to denote those properties, affects, or properties that mean something is wrong with you health-wise.
      interface  ItemCraftor
      This interface denotes an ability that also incidentally is capable of generating objects, usually items.
      interface  ItemTicker
      The interface for affects which cause an Item to rejuvenate after a particular amount of time.
      interface  Language
      A Language ability represents both the ability to understand one or more spoken or written languages, and the ability to speak one or more spoken languages.
      interface  LimbDamage
      An LimbDamage is a kind of ability that denotes missing, broken, or damaged body parts.
      interface  MendingSkill
      This interface denotes an ability that also incidentally is capable of mending objects, usually items or mobs.
      interface  Trap
      A trap is a kind of ability that behaves mostly like a property, in that it is not typically invoked as a skill, although there are skills that generate or make use of Trap abilities.
      interface  TriggeredAffect
      TriggeredAffect is an ability interface to denote those properties that are typically non-removable inherent attributes of the things they affect.
